<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="fascinate-v">fascinate <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'fæsɪneɪt/    美 /'fæsɪneɪt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>(使) 着迷；(使) 迷住</strong></h4>
<p>to attract or interest sb very much：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Mars has fascinated people since ancient times.
自古以来，火星就令人着迷。</p><footer>外研新选必② – 6</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It seems that the private lives of movie stars never fail to fascinate.
电影明星的私生活似乎总是让人津津乐道。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>fascinated /'fæsɪneɪtɪd/ adj   </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I was <strong>fascinated by</strong> her beautiful voice.
我被她美妙的声音迷住了。</p></div>

<p>fascination /ˌfæsɪ'neɪʃn/ n   </p></div>